<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate.ejs") %>
<body>
  <div class="container my-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-md-10">
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-center">Terms & Conditions</h1>
        <p class="text-muted text-center">
          Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>
        </p>

        <hr class="mb-4" />

        <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
        <p>
          Welcome to <strong>Wanderlust</strong>. Your privacy is important to
          us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your
          personal information when you use our travel platform.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, other
            login credentials
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Account Information:</strong> Login details, preferences,
            and saved itineraries.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on the
            website, and browser/device details.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. How We Use Your Information</h3>
        <p>Your information may be used to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services.</li>
          <li>Personalize your travel experience.</li>
          <li>Process bookings, reservations, and payments.</li>
          <li>Send important updates, offers, or notifications.</li>
          <li>
            Ensure safety, prevent fraud, and comply with legal obligations.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Sharing of Information</h3>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share data
          with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Service Providers:</strong> Trusted third parties that
            assist in payment, booking, or analytics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> If required to comply with law
            or protect user safety.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In case of a merger,
            acquisition, or restructuring.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Data Security</h3>
        <p>
          We use encryption, secure servers, and regular monitoring to protect
          your information. However, no system is 100% secure, and we cannot
          guarantee absolute protection.
        </p>

        <h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access, update, or delete your personal data.</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for marketing communications.</li>
          <li>Request a copy of the data we store about you.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7. Cookies Policy</h3>
        <p>
          Wanderlust uses cookies to improve website functionality and
          personalize content. You can manage or disable cookies through your
          browser settings.
        </p>

        <h3>8. Changes to This Policy</h3>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will
          be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date.
        </p>

        <h3>9. Contact Us</h3>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach us
          at:
        </p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@wanderlust.com</p>
        <p><strong>Phone:</strong> +91 12465 88319</p>
        <br />
        <input type="checkbox" id="terms" />
        <label for="terms"> I accept the terms and conditions </label>
        <br />
        <br />

        <form method="GET" action="/listings">
          <button id="submitLink">Submit</button>
        </form>

        <script>
          let checkBox = document.getElementById("terms");
          let submit = document.getElementById("submitLink");

          checkBox.addEventListener("change", () => {
            if (checkBox.checked) {
              submit.style.display = "inline";
            } else {
              submit.style.display = "none";
            }
          });
        </script>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
